# Sweet and Sour Chicken

## Ingredients

- Chicken, diced, 300g
- Red pepper, 150g
- Pineapple, 150g
- Ginger, 15g
- Garlic, 15g
- Ketchup,
- Soy sauce
- Rice vinegar
- Chilli jam
- Edamame beans, 150g
- Rice, uncooked 200g
- Sesame seeds

## Steps

1. Chop **red pepper**, **pineapple**, **ginger** and **garlic** and put in one bowl, "veg".
1. Combine **soy sauce**, **rice vinegar**, **ketchup**, **chilli jam** and put in another, "sauce".
1. In parallel:
11. Set the **rice** cooking
11. Boil **edamame beans** for 3mins and leave to one side
1. Fry **chicken** for around 3 mins
1. Add "veg" and fry for another 5 mins
1. Add "sauce" and fry for another 3mins
1. Combine the **rice** with the **edamame**.
1. Add a good sprinking of **sesame seeds** to serve
